{"parse":{"title":"Immigration tariff","pageid":15493630,"revid":811723684,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>An <b>immigration tariff</b> is a <a href=\"/wiki/Duty_(economics)\" title=\"Duty (economics)\">charge levied</a> on <a href=\"/wiki/Immigrants\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Immigrants\">immigrants</a> wanting <a href=\"/wiki/Permanent_residency\" title=\"Permanent residency\">permanent residency</a> within a nation. As a means of applying <a href=\"/wiki/Price_theory\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Price theory\">price theory</a> to a nation's <a href=\"/wiki/Immigration_policy\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Immigration policy\">immigration policy</a>, it is generally advocated as an alternative to existing <a href=\"/wiki/Regulations\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Regulations\">bureaucratic procedures</a> as a means of moderating or better regulating the flow of immigration to a given level. \n</p><p>The idea is frequently associated with American <a href=\"/wiki/Economist\" title=\"Economist\">economist</a> <a href=\"/wiki/Gary_Becker\" title=\"Gary Becker\">Gary Becker</a>, who stated, \"When I mention this to people, they sometimes go hysterical.\" <sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p><a href=\"/wiki/Alex_Nowrasteh\" title=\"Alex Nowrasteh\">Alex Nowrasteh</a>, an immigration policy analyst, wrote a policy analysis arguing for immigration tariffs for the <a href=\"/wiki/Competitive_Enterprise_Institute\" title=\"Competitive Enterprise Institute\">Competitive Enterprise Institute</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>In March 2015 the Australian government launched an inquiry into the use of an immigration tariff as an alternative to existing immigration arrangements.<sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p><br />\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"See_also\">See also</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Immigration_tariff&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: See also\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li><a href=\"/wiki/Tariff\" title=\"Tariff\">Tariff</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/United_States_Permanent_Resident_Card\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"United States Permanent Resident Card\">Green card</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Permanent_residency\" title=\"Permanent residency\">Permanent residency</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Visa_(document)\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Visa (document)\">Immigrant visa</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Immigration_law\" title=\"Immigration law\">Immigration law</a> (for a broader discussion of the topic of <a href=\"/wiki/Immigration\" title=\"Immigration\">Immigration</a>)</li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Migrant_levy\" title=\"Migrant levy\">Migrant levy</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Gary_Becker\" title=\"Gary Becker\">Gary Becker</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Eric_Weinstein\" title=\"Eric Weinstein\">Eric Weinstein</a></li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Immigration_tariff&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation web\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.chicagobooth.edu/news/2007-04-02_Becker-bb.aspx\">\"Gary Beck on immigration tariffs\"</a>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%